    All Classes and Interfaces

    Classes
    Class
    Description
    AdminHomePage
    AdminPage class represents the user interface for the admin user.
    AdminSetupPage
    The SetupAdmin class handles the setup process for creating an administrator account.
    Answer
    The Answer class represents an answer submitted by a user in response to a Question.
    Answers
    The Answers class manages a list of Answer objects associated with a single Question.
    DatabaseHelper
    The DatabaseHelper class is responsible for managing the connection to the database, performing operations such as user registration, login validation, and handling invitation codes.
    FirstPage
    FirstPage class represents the initial screen for the first user.
    HWCRUDTest
    HWCRUDTest Verifies the CRUD operations and in-memory behaviors supporting six staff user stories.
    Interaction
    Represents a unified "interaction" in the system, which may be either a question or an answer (or potentially feedback in the future).
    InvitationPage
    InvitePage class represents the page where an admin can generate an invitation code.
    PasswordEvaluator
     
    QASystemDatabase
     
    Question
    The Question class represents a question submitted by a user.
    Questions
    The Questions class manages a list of Question objects.
    Review
     
    ReviewerHomePage
    This class represents the home page for a reviewer in the Question Answer System application.
    SetupAccountPage
    SetupAccountPage class handles the account setup process for new users.
    SetupLoginSelectionPage
    The SetupLoginSelectionPage class allows users to choose between setting up a new account or logging into an existing account.
    StaffHomePage
    StaffHomePage Now includes: - Filter Interactions by type (All, question, answer) - Sort Interactions by content (asc/desc) - Flag Interactions - Add Internal Notes - Search Interactions by keyword in username or content (User Story #6)
    StartCSE360
     
    StudentHomePage
    This page displays the student's home page, showing existing questions, allowing students to post new questions and answer existing ones, and providing a filter for resolved answers.
    User
    The User class represents a user entity in the system.
    UserHomePage
    This page displays a simple welcome message for the user.
    UserLoginPage
    The UserLoginPage class provides a login interface for users to access their accounts.
    UserNameRecognizer
     
    WelcomeLoginPage
    The WelcomeLoginPage class displays a welcome screen for authenticated users.
